“With the support of the UK government, donors, national governments and Global Citizen members like you, we can make social injustice like malnutrition a thing of the past,” Tracey Ullman, Ambassador of Power of Nutrition, said during a live concert in London in April 2018.
The group also said that after implementing more than 5,000 actions calling on the UK to improve the quality of maternal and child nutrition, the government announced funding for the Power of Nutrition project, which will reach 5 million women and children with nutritional problems.
One of the most frequently asked questions on their website was, “How can we be sure that extreme poverty will be eradicated?”
Global citizen responded as follows: “It’s going to be a long and difficult road —sometimes we stumble and fail.
But as with the once great civil rights and anti-apartheid movements, we will succeed because together we are stronger.
