The usual host of this broadcast for many years, Kirsty Young, took a few months off due to illness.
Appearing on the show for the first time hosted by Laverne, Daley said that growing up, he felt “less valuable” than others because “the simultaneous liking of boys and girls was not socially acceptable.”
He said, “To this day, this feeling of being less valuable and being different is something that gives me the strength to succeed.”
He said he wanted to prove he was “something” so as not to disappoint everyone when they finally found out about his sexuality.
The two-time Olympic bronze medalist has become a vocal activist for the LGBT community and used his performance at this year’s Commonwealth Games in Australia to appeal to more countries to decriminalize homosexuality.
He said he chose to express himself because he felt happy, able to live openly, without any implications, and wanted to give others “hope.”
