Daley married an Oscar winner (who is 20 years his senior) last year, noting that the age difference was never a problem for him.
“When you go through so much at such a young age,” he meant his first Olympics at the age of 14 and his father’s death from cancer three years later, “he said that it was difficult for him to find someone at the same age who had experienced similar ups and downs.
The couple became the parents of a boy named Robert Ray Black-Daley in June. Daley said that his perception of certain things has completely changed.
“The most important thing for me last year was to win a gold medal,” he said.
“And you know what? There are more important things than Olympic gold medals.
